		<title>05Homelessness(1)</title>
		<content>Over 1,700 single people are living in 
hostels in Tower Hamlets.              
An unknown number sleep rough on the   
streets,in 'skippers' or squats.       
An unknown number 'crash' on floors    
with friends or relatives.             
There are 5,000 awaiting single person 
housing in Tower Hamlets.              
The rise of TB in the borough is seen  
and is acknowledged as symptomatic of  
deteriorating housing conditions.The   
disease is closely and historically    
linked with slum housing,poverty and   
overcrowding.                          
                                       
Susan Masters(11)                      
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
